[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'completing in this tutorial. To do the extension is very simple. Now, I\'m going to demonstrate this on Dreamina, but as long as you have access to Omni reference or the ability to upload references, especially videos, this is how you do it. You basically'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'upload your video as a reference. So, this is the video that I first generated, and this was generated at a resolution of 1080p. You can see over here, I just dragged and dropped my video to upload it. And I would recommend using Dreamina Seedons 2.0 to'

[03:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'get the best results. There is the fast and mini, which uses less credits, but if you want the best results, go for the standard version. Now, this is important, right? If you\'re doing an extension, like I said, my video was generated at 1080p. I want to make sure'

[03:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'my extension is also at 1080p because if I put it on 720p, you know, to save some credits, there\'s going to be a very distinct jump in quality of that extension. So, keep it 1080p to get the best results. And then,'

[03:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'I\'m going to make sure that, you know, it matches the length of my video clip. In this case, it\'s also 15 seconds, so that\'s good to go. It is quite pricey on credits, to be honest. And then, to break down the prompt, once you\'ve'

[03:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'uploaded your video, the most important thing to put at the start of the prompt is the scene continues because the AI is smart enough to analyze this video and see exactly where it ends, and then it\'s going to continue from where that video'

[03:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'ended. It\'s going to copy over the motion. It\'s going to remember what characters it sees, the environment, and even any voices that were present. So, it\'s an extremely powerful feature. So, just to break that down one more'

[04:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'time and to also give you a bonus tip, whenever you upload your video as an omni reference and you type the scene continues, you\'ll be generating what happens next or what\'s going to be happening in the future. But, if you also type show me what happens before,'

[04:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'you can generate the sequence that\'s going to take place before your video actually starts, which allows you to generate an event that happened in the past. And you can connect both past, present, and future scenes together and'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'connect them all together to create a beautiful and consistent narrative. Another super powerful tip that I want to give you guys, uh you\'ll notice over here with my extension, throughout the duration of this video, her mouth is'

[04:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'concealed, but my character actually has a mole on her face. And if I just extended right now, the AI would not know that because obviously it can\'t see the mole. So, you could upload your video in addition with your character so'

[04:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'that the AI knows what your what your character looks like. You can see, there\'s the mole. So, now as I\'m prompting over here, you know, she\'s going to be removing her hand from her mouth, uh you\'ll notice that in this video, uh let me just scroll scroll'

[05:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'back, you can actually see the mole present. Uh so, that\'s super powerful. If you want con- you know, continuity uh with consistency with your characters, you can even attach that as an image reference. And I\'ve mentioned that in my'

