VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'prompt over here that this is the person\'s identity and I just mentioned that image. So, that\'s a great way to keep continuity of your characters also when you are extending videos. Now, I\'m all about transparency on this'

[05:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'channel and I do want to talk about limitations. Number one, right, when we do in extensions, of course, we can extend a video, but at the moment Seed runs 2.0 does not have a dedicated extend button that can do it seamlessly. So, we have to put in some extra work'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'right now and do all of this, you know, manual editing in an editing software. So, if you want to do a seamless extension, you will need an editing program. And I use CapCut, and that\'s what I\'m going to be using in this'

[05:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'video. It\'s super easy to use. Number two, probably the most important, uh video quality is going to degrade over multiple extensions. So, if you\'re taking the same clip and you keep extending and keep extending, you are going to notice the quality dropping.'

[06:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'That\'s why I said at the start it\'s important that you generate your next clip at the exact same resolution so that it tries to keep it as close as possible, but you will see some degradation over time. So, keep that in'

[06:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'mind. Um you can be strategic with this. Maybe you can insert some other shots or B-roll um throughout your narrative uh to counter this. Uh but there will be degradation until ByteDance and SeaArt'

[06:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '2.0 fix this so that it always extends with the same quality. Another thing is when you extend a video, you will see that the contrast and the or the exposure can actually change. And this'

[06:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'is why you need to know how to do some color grading uh in your editing software to get it to match as closely as possible because if there\'s a massive contrast uh shift, uh and you know, the video is seamless, that alone can also'

[06:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'be quite jarring. Uh so, that\'s another thing to keep in mind. And the last limitation is that audio uh usually it blends quite seamlessly between the two clips, but sometimes you have to be'

[07:10] [scene:talk]
