AUDIO: 'there we go, that is seamless. And that\'s basically how you do a seamless extension. All right, so trying to create that seamless, you know, transition between the two clips is the first hurdle, but'

[11:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'another one you\'ll actually encounter is the audio because remember, these are two clips that are overlapping each other and sometimes it can create a very weird transition with audio. So, what I do is with my first clip, I\'ll actually add a bit of a fade out. I\'ll say maybe'

[11:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '0.5. So, the way this is working is that when the clip gets to this point, the audio is actually going to fade out and then seamlessly transition into the second clip\'s audio, and that makes it a lot less noticeable that there was an'

[11:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'extension here or another clip visible. So, that\'s just one way to counter any inconsistencies with the audio. So, now if I click on play There we go. In my opinion, it sounds'

[12:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'less noticeable that there were two clips overlapping each other. So, add a bit of a fade out. Something else you can also do over here to mask any inconsistencies is to actually add some ambient audio. You could use a website'

